        <div class="container">
            <div class="columns">
                <div class="column">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h1 class="title">About</h1>
                        <h2 class="subtitle">About the service</h2>
                    
                        <p class="block">
                            The CompSoc Email Studio allows for the easy creation
                            of nicely formatted emails. It automatically strings
                            together an MJML formatter with our email system, Sendy.
                        </p>

                        <p class="block">
                            Please report any bugs <a href="https://github.com/compsoc-edinburgh/email-studio/issues/new">on Github</a>,
                            or bother @kage on Discord.
                        </p>

                    </div>
                    <div class="block">
                        <h1 class="title">MJML</h1>
                        <h2 class="subtitle">About MJML</h2>

                        <p class="block">
                            MJML is Mailjet's email templating engine. Writing
                            email HTML by hand sucks, so MJML lets us write emails
                            in an XML format which is then compiled to HTML
                            compatible with most email clients. 
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            <a href="//documentation.mjml.io" target="_blank">View the MJML documentation here.</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="block">
                        <h1 class="title">Assets</h1>
                        <h2 class="subtitle">About the Asset store</h2>

                        <p class="block">
                            Instead of attaching images to the email, we leverage
                            our existing object storage infrastructure to serve
                            static files. Use the Assets interface to upload images
                            for inclusion in the emails. Assets can be linked into
                            emails by referring to them with <code>@asset:asset_name</code>.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="column is-two-thirds">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h1 class="title">Sendy</h1>
                        <h2 class="subtitle">Sendy-specific shortcuts</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="block">
                        <p>
                            Sendy is our email engine. It handles the actual sending
                            of the email, and performs the second step in the email
                            templating. It supports more subscriber-based templating,
                            and knows about the email list. Here are a list of
                            supported templating instructions; note that these will
                            not be interpolated in the MJML preview&mdash;but they will
                            be in the Sendy output (you can verify this in the Sendy preview).
                        </p>
                    </div>

